data.title: The most fun we had! Magical!
data.text: John the owner magician is a real treat and made us feel special. The magic is amazing! So much fun we went back 2 times in one night!

data.title: Wow.....Just Wow!
data.text: What an absolutely fun time at this micro beer and wine bar.  John, the engaging and magical proprietor is a joy to meet and absolutely fantastic to spend time with.  His slight of hand will leave you wondering "What just happened?" as he ties in his unique brand of magic to what he has learned about his customers during the brief time you've conversed.  I went twice in one night, once when our foursome were the only clients in the early evening, and again later at night when he played to a full bar.  Both visits were fantastic.  I can't wait to visit again during my next trip to St. Pete.

data.title: What a gem!
data.text: Absolutely a great experience! Great drinks and great atmosphere....plus he does MAGIC! This is a must go!

data.title: Unique experience
data.text: This bar completely blends into the background, so if you're not looking for it you'd probably walk right past it. John is lots of fun and does some amazing up-close sleight-of-hand magic. Fun selection of drinks, including sake. Cozy and intimate setting. Unfortunately an obnoxious pedal pub group intruded on the personal experience, but they left after awhile. If you're looking for something unique and different, I'd highly recommend.

data.title: Fun magical bar
data.text: John, the bartender/owner/magician is great, lots of fun. The bar is very small but it makes it kind of cozy too. Bar serves beer, wine and a champagne/wine drink. Food can be ordered from the next door Vietnamese Restaurant (good food) if you want to snack there. John is entertaining as he just keeps the magic surprises coming.
